Label: MTRF1L, ICT1
Comment: Both MTRF1L and ICT1 can bind a standard stop codon in the A-site of the ribosome and cause release of the polypeptide. ICT1 can also cause release of ribosomes stalled in non-standard conformations (e.g. non-standard stop codons, mRNA lacking a stop codon) (inferred from pig mitoribosomes in Akabane et al. 2014).

Label: mRNA
Comment: Mitochondrial mRNAs are characterized by lacking or having very short (1-3 nucleotide) untranslated leaders and no introns. The mitochondrial genome of humans encodes only 13 polypeptides.
